For the purposes of this solicitation, direct integration with third-party applications not integrated through the
security group model currently deployed should be considered in-scope functionality.
6.3
REQUIREMENTS AND SCOPE OF WORK
Objectives
The objective of the County is to streamline and automate the onboarding, offboarding and transfer processes for
both full-time County workforce members as well as contractor and vendor accounts. In addition, the County is
interested in providing a platform to efficiently process user system access changes. Furthermore, the County is
interested in leveraging existing licensing to reduce costs associated with our SSO platform and therefore it will be
replaced with Entra SSO as part of this solicitation. Finally, respondents should be prepared to enhance any active
directory synchronization services currently in-place to complete the IAM and SSO implementations.
The County is seeking a strong and highly experienced implementer for the Entra platforms. It is expected that
respondents will work closely with subject matter experts on Workday, ServiceNow, Active Directory, Azure,
Microsoft licensing, current single sign-on (SSO) application, and any other resource needed to accurately discover
workflows, constraints and requirements to implement the following functions:
1.
Assess Active Directory and Entra ID Sync
Validate readiness for IAM automation and SSO replacement.
Analyze AD settings and configurations for best practice and secure design.
Evaluate domain, OU structure, role-based access control (RBAC)/delegation, security group
strategy.
Identify and remove stale objects and lifecycle inconsistencies.
Ensure the identity ecosystem (Entra/AD) is configured to support IAM, and in alignment with
best practice synchronization designs.
Identify misconfiguration, risks, and remediation needs.
2. Replace current SSO
Ensure all currently integrated applications are migrated to Entra SSO with minimal service
interruptions.
Ensure all user presentation and authentication processes are migrated to Entra SSO with
minimal service interruptions or user interaction.
Manage and coordinate all communications to minimize impact to system access.
3. Implement IAM Automation
Automate workforce onboarding, offboarding, transfers, and system/resource access change
assignments.
System should support County employee, contractor/vendor lifecycles.
Perform process discovery as needed to automate workflow approvals to ensure timely
completion based on user requested Workday or ServiceNow requested effective dates for
onboarding/offboarding and transfers.
Implement or replace existing systems as needed to streamline IAM integrations and leverage
existing investments in Microsoft licensing to reduce costs on third party platforms performing
same or similar functions.
4. Integrate IAM with Workday and ServiceNow
Workday -> IAM for employee lifecycle management.
ServiceNow -> IAM for contractors/vendors on/offboarding and application access changes (all
workforce members).
5. Automate Application Provisioning
