Assign basic application access to new or transferred users, determined by department and or
position classification.
Automate necessary workflow approval notifications as needed when onboarding/offboarding
or transferring employees, contractors or vendors.
Automate workflow routing of required approvals for application access or elevated rights
requests.
Provide a platform/portal to easily request and automate user system access changes to access
new systems, remove access from systems, or modify approved authorization levels from
integrated applications. This may also require the platform to open, process and close a
Service Now ticket request to retain request records in the current service request platform.
6. Strengthening Compliance & Governance
Provide additional protections to maintain least privilege access based on data/application
owner (approver) authorized levels.
Enforce contractor account expiration dates with an automated option to extend, with
requisite approvals and authorizations.
7. Provide Documentation, Training, and transition to Operations
Operational runbooks.
Architecture diagrams.
Knowledge transfer sessions.
Create Knowledge Base articles, and other material, or training engagements designed to fully
transfer support knowledge to County TSD workforce members.
As part of the proposal, the proposer must provide a strategy to meet the following goals:
Discover/obtain all necessary information required to achieve the objectives outlined in this solicitation.
Integrate IAM into the County computing ecosystem to automate on/offboard and employee transfers.
Evaluate data accuracy, consistency, and integrity within the AD domain and forest environments.
Resolve any functional active directory synchronization issues that might hinder or overcomplicate the
objectives identified in this solicitation.
Leverage all current County Microsoft licensing levels whenever possible.
Provide an IAM portal to facilitate user access changes and integrated with pre-defined authorizations
and approvals as needed on a case-by-case basis.
Provide methodology in which stakeholders will have visibility into the progress of their requests for
on/offboarding and transfers and application change requests.
Provide a phased system and function delivery approach that is both adaptive and agile to minimize user
and system access disruptions and to allow the County to adjust implementation strategy as needed.
Educate and train current support personnel on the IAM, and SSO administrative tasks required to sustain
the proposed platform and related infrastructure.
Provide sufficient documentation and educational materials so that the County can educate our
workforce management resources, such as the departmental payroll resource coordinators (PRCs), on
how to effectively utilize any implemented IAM or SSO platforms, portals or other services included in the
respondent's solution.
6.4
PERFORMANCE MEASURE
The following are specific performance measures required:
Successfully leverage licensed software that will increase efficiency and performance while reducing costs.
Demonstrate successful integration with Workday and ServiceNow for the automation of workforce
member on/off boarding and transfers.
Demonstrate operation efficiency and capability to provide just in time functional changes based on
request effective date as reflected in Workday and ServiceNow.
RFP# TSD-20261923
23
Rev 12/15/2025
Demonstrate workforce member revocation of rights and access to integrated applications upon
successful offboarding.
Successfully implement and demonstrate approval workflows with escalation processes designed to
obtain authorization for changes to workforce member access to applications and resources.
Successfully implement a replacement SSO platform with minimal impact to users or integrated
organizations.
Audit and report on existing on-prem environment against best practices to determine if there are
orphaned accounts or resource objects that should be removed.
Sufficiently demonstrate integration and synchronization of on-prem active directory services with Entra
ID to ensure all end-state cloud-based systems operate effectively and efficiently.
Provide documentation on system administration and change processes to ensure that the system
maintains the efficient automation processes regardless of changing system of record processes.
6.5
FINGERPRINTING AND BACKGROUND CHECKS
In some instances, may be required if the proposed contract requires access to certain sensitive groups or
