        "basisOfEstimate": "This is a formal RFP (TSD-20261923) from the County of San Mateo for implementing Microsoft's Identity & Access Management (IAM) solution with a government-stated estimated value of $300,000-$500,000 over 36 months base period plus two 12-month option years (60 months total). The contract type is not explicitly stated but the Price Proposal Template structure (Professional Services with roles, quantities, per-item costs across Years 1-5) and the fixed-scope nature of the implementation suggest a Fixed-Price or hybrid structure. Price carries only 25% weight in Phase I evaluation (best-value procurement), with Method/Approach at 45% and Experience at 30%. Phase II is a demonstration/interview worth 100 points. CRITICAL INDUSTRY MISMATCH: Horus Technology is an AWS Advanced Consulting Partner specializing in document automation, cloud-native development, and AI/ML solutions. This solicitation requires deep Microsoft ecosystem expertise \u2014 specifically Microsoft Entra ID (formerly Azure AD), identity lifecycle management, Workday/ServiceNow integration, SAML SSO, MFA migration, and identity governance workflows. The company's knowledge base, past performance, and content library contain zero references to Microsoft IAM, Entra ID, Azure AD, or identity governance implementations. The organization's provided labor rates (Software Engineer $171.40/hr, Manufacturing Engineer $178.89/hr, QA $16.86/hr) do not correspond to the specialized Microsoft IAM roles this engagement requires. The BOM items (software license and subcontractor entries labeled 'test') appear to be placeholder data and are not relevant. Because Horus Technology fundamentally cannot meet the minimum qualifications (3 years Microsoft IAM experience, 3 government IAM implementations in 5 years), totalPrice is set to $0 \u2014 submitting a price would be inappropriate as the proposal would be deemed non-responsive at the minimum qualifications gate.",
