        "basisOfEstimate": "This is a formal RFP (RFP No. 26-22) from San Bernardino City Unified School District seeking a hosted, integrated data warehouse and business intelligence/analytics platform solution. NO government estimated value is provided in the solicitation. Organization labor rates are provided (Software Engineer: $171.40/hr, Manufacturing Engineer: $178.89/hr, QA: $16.86/hr) but are IRRELEVANT because this solicitation seeks an existing commercial SaaS product, not custom software development services. The pricing structure is product-based: per-student annual licensing (~44,000 students), hosting fees, one-time implementation fees, and training hours. HORUSTECH is a custom software development firm with AWS expertise but does NOT have an existing K-12 data warehouse/BI platform product. The District is currently using PowerSchool Analytics/Unified Insights and is seeking a replacement or upgrade \u2014 competitors will be established EdTech BI vendors (e.g., Tableau/Salesforce Education, PowerSchool, Schoolzilla/Renaissance, Clever Analytics, Otus, Panorama Education, etc.) with mature products and per-student pricing models. The organization's past performance includes an educational data platform for DegreeData ($800K) focused on document processing/credential verification, which is tangentially related but fundamentally different from a district-wide BI/analytics platform. Total price is set to $0 because the organization cannot competitively price an existing product it does not have. Price confidence is set to 18 (very low) reflecting the fundamental industry/product mismatch.",
        "materialCostTotal": 0,
        "assumptions": [
          "This solicitation requires an existing commercial data warehouse and BI platform product, not custom software development services.",
